channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Hunter Biden's trial on federal gun charges
item.description: Hunter Biden's trial on gun charges is underway in Delaware. The president's son faces three charges in the case brought by the special counsel. Follow here for the latest live news updates

item.title: Remains of World War II soldier identified, returned home to Buffalo
item.description: U.S. Army Pfc. Bartholomew Loschiavo of Buffalo, New York, was killed in action on Oct. 1, 1944, while his unit engaged German troops in Luxembourg.

item.title: Claudia Sheinbaum projected to be Mexico's first woman president
item.description: Claudia Sheinbaum is projected to win Mexico's presidential election and become the first woman to lead the country's government, according to preliminary results.

item.title: Elderly woman killed after suspect carjacks vehicle, crashes into building: Police
item.description: An elderly woman was killed after a suspect stole the vehicle she was a passenger in and then crashed into a building in Washington, D.C., police said.

item.title: Georgia court sets tentative Oct. 4 date to hear Trump appeal of Willis ruling
item.description: The Georgia Court of Appeals has tentatively set arguments for Oct. 4 in an effort by former President Donald Trump to remove Fulton County District Attorney Fani Willis from the 2020 election-related case.

item.title: Fauci testifies on the origins of Covid-19
item.description: Dr. Anthony Fauci, the former director of the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases, is expected to testify at a House subcommittee hearing about the US' Covid-19 pandemic response, policies and transparency. Follow for live updates.

item.title: Trump appeal in Georgia case set for October, likely pushing trial past election
item.description: The Georgia Court of Appeals has tentatively scheduled oral arguments on Donald Trump's the appeal of the Fani Willis disqualification ruling for October.
